-- Morgan Stanley Hires BNP Paribas's Hiratsuka as Director for Japan Equity
-- Shunichi Ozasa
-- 2010-07-01T01:27:57Z
-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2010-07-01/morgan-stanley-hires-bnp-paribas-s-hiratsuka-as-director-for-japan-equity.html

          
          
             Morgan Stanley said it hired  Motomi Hiratsuka  from  BNP Paribas FP  as an executive director for its
equity business in Japan.  
 Hiratsuka, 44, joined Morgan Stanley MUFG Securities Co., a
joint venture with  Mitsubishi UFJ Financial Group Inc. , this
week, said  Mika Watanabe , a Tokyo-based spokeswoman for the
venture, without commenting further. Hiratsuka was formerly a
sales director in global equity and commodity derivatives at BNP
Paribas in Tokyo.  
 New York-based Morgan Stanley and Mitsubishi UFJ started
two joint ventures in May for investment banking and trading.
Teaming up with Mitsubishi UFJ, which invested $9 billion in the
Wall Street firm in 2008, may help Morgan Stanley bolster its
ranking in underwriting securities and advising on Japanese
mergers.  
 Hiratsuka joined Daiwa Securities Group Inc.â€™s brokerage
unit in 1989 after graduating from  Tokyo University of Science .
He joined BNP Paribas in 2002 after working at Goldman Sachs
Group Inc. in Tokyo.  
